The Vice President of the United States has invited important individuals to discuss their experiences and how the United States and its allies can support those who have been displaced by the conflict in Ukraine. The Vice President recently met with the President of Poland to discuss their commitment to assisting individuals and families who have fled Ukraine. The conversation aims to inform the Vice President, the President of the United States, and the American people about the experiences of those affected so that they can provide the best support. The Vice President emphasizes that those who have fled Ukraine are not alone and that people around the world are watching and expressing their support. The press will leave before the conversation begins.